WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.org ] ==-

2
00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.372
- Is it a girl?
- Yes.

3
00:00:52.502 --> 00:00:55.456
- Show me its arm.
- She bears the mark.

4
00:00:55.589 --> 00:00:57.747
No!

5
00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:03.508
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

6
00:01:05.807 --> 00:01:08.096
- Please help me!
- I can't.

7
00:01:08.227 --> 00:01:10.634
They're going to kill her.

8
00:01:14.942 --> 00:01:17.515
Please! Please!

9
00:01:20.113 --> 00:01:23.613
Oh. thank you. Ethna.
Thank you.

10
00:01:31.583 --> 00:01:34.157
Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!

11
00:01:58.735 --> 00:02:00.942
You cannot stop the prophecy!

12
00:02:01.071 --> 00:02:04.155
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

13
00:02:04.283 --> 00:02:06.571
No. No!

14
00:02:06.702 --> 00:02:08.990
Where's the baby?

15
00:02:09.121 --> 00:02:11.576
- The midwife.
- Find that baby. Sorsha.

16
00:02:11.707 --> 00:02:15.040
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

17
00:02:15.168 --> 00:02:17.244
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

18
00:02:17.379 --> 00:02:19.418
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

19
00:02:19.548 --> 00:02:23.047
- My baby will finish you!
- Kill her.

20
00:05:50.425 --> 00:05:52.382
Dada! Dada!

21
00:05:55.805 --> 00:05:57.882
- Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!

22
00:06:00.393 --> 00:06:03.560
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

23
00:06:03.688 --> 00:06:05.562
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

24
00:06:05.690 --> 00:06:07.849
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

25
00:06:13.573 --> 00:06:15.400
Come on.

26
00:06:18.286 --> 00:06:20.860
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

27
00:06:20.997 --> 00:06:23.832
But. Dada. it's a baby.

28
00:06:23.959 --> 00:06:28.704
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

29
00:06:28.838 --> 00:06:32.338
- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?

30
00:06:32.467 --> 00:06:36.216
Daikinis are big.
Giants who live far away.

31
00:06:38.098 --> 00:06:40.340
She's so cute.

32
00:06:40.475 --> 00:06:43.393
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

33
00:06:44.980 --> 00:06:49.725
We'll push it downstream
and forget we ever saw it. Come on.

34
00:06:49.859 --> 00:06:51.733
Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

35
00:06:52.988 --> 00:06:55.989
It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

36
00:06:56.116 --> 00:06:59.449
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

37
00:07:01.121 --> 00:07:05.617
Mr Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!

38
00:07:10.922 --> 00:07:13.793
Ufgood. you still haven't paid
your debts to me.

39
00:07:13.925 --> 00:07:15.965
Where did you get these seeds?

40
00:07:16.094 --> 00:07:18.763
Well. maybe I used magic.

41
00:07:19.973 --> 00:07:22.808
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

42
00:07:22.934 --> 00:07:26.434
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

43
00:07:26.563 --> 00:07:29.979
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

44
00:07:30.108 --> 00:07:33.062
There's no law against that.
Mr Burglekutt.

45
00:07:33.194 --> 00:07:36.610
Willow. you didn't leave them
alone by the river?

46
00:07:38.325 --> 00:07:39.320
Magic?

47
00:07:39.451 --> 00:07:43.069
You'll need magic to get your planting
done before the rains start.

48
00:07:45.248 --> 00:07:47.122
I will have this land. Ufgood...

49
00:07:47.250 --> 00:07:50.749
and you're gonna end up
working in the mines.

50
00:08:01.181 --> 00:08:02.805
You're lovely.

51
00:08:02.932 --> 00:08:04.890
Yes. you are.

52
00:08:05.018 --> 00:08:06.512
Kiaya!

53
00:08:07.520 --> 00:08:09.394
Oh. Willow!

54
00:08:09.522 --> 00:08:10.637
Good girl.

55
00:08:10.774 --> 00:08:14.392
Absolutely.
under no condition whatsoever...

56
00:08:14.527 --> 00:08:17.197
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

57
00:08:17.322 --> 00:08:21.984
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on.

58
00:08:22.118 --> 00:08:24.111
There we are. Come on.

59
00:08:24.245 --> 00:08:26.997
Hey. I will not be ignored!

60
00:08:27.374 --> 00:08:29.662
Mims? Ranon?

61
00:08:42.138 --> 00:08:44.712
You're gonna be all clean.

62
00:08:51.106 --> 00:08:53.727
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

63
00:08:53.858 --> 00:08:56.349
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

64
00:08:56.486 --> 00:08:59.273
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

65
00:08:59.406 --> 00:09:02.241
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?"

66
00:09:02.367 --> 00:09:05.321
"That's right. And he's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!"

67
00:09:05.453 --> 00:09:07.362
Willow. calm down.

68
00:09:07.497 --> 00:09:09.490
Calm down?

69
00:09:09.624 --> 00:09:11.617
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

70
00:09:11.751 --> 00:09:15.416
Love. the High Aldwin hasn't picked
a new apprentice in years.

71
00:09:15.547 --> 00:09:18.713
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

72
00:09:21.594 --> 00:09:25.177
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

73
00:09:25.306 --> 00:09:28.058
Hold her while I get some milk.

74
00:09:35.734 --> 00:09:38.225
Dada. she likes you.

75
00:09:47.787 --> 00:09:49.412
Bye.

76
00:09:50.957 --> 00:09:53.080
Come on. kids. Let's go.

77
00:10:00.508 --> 00:10:04.091
I will now magically join the rings!

78
00:10:33.166 --> 00:10:34.577
Thank you. son.

79
00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:39.709
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

80
00:10:56.147 --> 00:10:58.306
Give me a ripe one. Good.

81
00:11:04.656 --> 00:11:08.819
And now.
for my final amazing feat...

82
00:11:08.952 --> 00:11:13.281
I will make
this entire pig disappear!

83
00:11:23.842 --> 00:11:27.211
Please watch very closely.

84
00:11:27.345 --> 00:11:31.129
<i>Wuppity bairn. deru. deru!</i>

85
00:11:36.729 --> 00:11:38.805
What happened to your pig?

86
00:11:40.316 --> 00:11:43.270
No!
Hey. come here. you!

87
00:11:47.824 --> 00:11:49.863
I seen enough.

88
00:12:06.342 --> 00:12:07.718
Attention!

89
00:12:08.428 --> 00:12:12.556
The High Aldwin will now make his choice
for his new apprentice!

90
00:12:12.682 --> 00:12:16.098
Bring forth the hopefuls.

91
00:12:16.227 --> 00:12:18.552
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

92
00:12:18.688 --> 00:12:22.389
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

93
00:12:22.525 --> 00:12:24.981
Is this a joke?

94
00:12:32.994 --> 00:12:37.407
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

95
00:12:38.041 --> 00:12:42.038
Forget all you know
or think you know.

96
00:12:42.170 --> 00:12:46.120
All that you require
is your intuition.

97
00:12:46.257 --> 00:12:50.337
Now. the power
to control the world...

98
00:12:50.470 --> 00:12:53.720
is in which finger?

99
00:13:37.809 --> 00:13:40.300
No apprentice this year!

100
00:14:01.874 --> 00:14:05.208
- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!

101
00:14:05.336 --> 00:14:08.171
Take Ranon in there. quick!

102
00:14:16.139 --> 00:14:17.763
Mims!

103
00:14:36.951 --> 00:14:38.695
I'm scared. Dada!

104
00:14:50.298 --> 00:14:52.836
Come on!

105
00:15:10.568 --> 00:15:12.395
Vohnkar!

106
00:15:23.039 --> 00:15:25.909
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

107
00:15:28.294 --> 00:15:30.037
Dada! Dada!

108
00:15:33.424 --> 00:15:35.631
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

109
00:15:39.388 --> 00:15:42.389
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

110
00:15:54.445 --> 00:15:56.272
I'm here.

111
00:16:04.205 --> 00:16:06.244
We can't keep the baby. Kiaya.

112
00:16:06.374 --> 00:16:09.125
We have to take her
to the village council.

113
00:16:22.640 --> 00:16:24.265
Silence!

114
00:16:24.392 --> 00:16:27.595
One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

115
00:16:27.728 --> 00:16:29.935
And you can be assured
that they won't give up...

116
00:16:30.064 --> 00:16:32.104
until they find
what they're looking for!

117
00:16:32.233 --> 00:16:35.436
- It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?

118
00:16:35.570 --> 00:16:37.977
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

119
00:16:40.324 --> 00:16:42.898
In the pit! In the pit!

120
00:16:48.040 --> 00:16:50.080
Willow.

121
00:16:50.209 --> 00:16:51.703
Willow Ufgood.

122
00:16:53.963 --> 00:16:55.754
Come forward.

123
00:17:02.305 --> 00:17:06.634
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

124
00:17:12.398 --> 00:17:14.474
A Daikini child.

125
00:17:14.650 --> 00:17:17.568
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

126
00:17:19.113 --> 00:17:22.316
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

127
00:17:22.450 --> 00:17:25.071
This child is special!

128
00:17:25.995 --> 00:17:29.446
This child must be taken
beyond the boundaries of our village.

129
00:17:29.582 --> 00:17:32.583
All the way across
the great river...

130
00:17:32.710 --> 00:17:34.750
to the Daikini crossroads.

131
00:17:34.879 --> 00:17:37.286
Well. who'll do that?

132
00:17:37.840 --> 00:17:40.212
It seems only fair...

133
00:17:40.343 --> 00:17:42.798
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

134
00:17:42.929 --> 00:17:45.929
be the very man
who plucked it out of the river.

135
00:17:47.642 --> 00:17:50.180
I nominate Willow Ufgood.

136
00:17:50.311 --> 00:17:51.474
No!

137
00:17:52.939 --> 00:17:55.346
I will consult the bones!

138
00:18:04.367 --> 00:18:07.368
The bones tell me nothing.

139
00:18:12.583 --> 00:18:14.825
Do you have any love
for this child?

140
00:18:23.678 --> 00:18:25.088
Yes.

141
00:18:26.389 --> 00:18:27.799
Yes. I do.

142
00:18:27.932 --> 00:18:30.933
The bones have spoken!

143
00:18:32.395 --> 00:18:36.309
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

144
00:18:36.440 --> 00:18:40.485
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

145
00:18:40.611 --> 00:18:43.067
But you will need help.

146
00:18:43.197 --> 00:18:48.404
Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?

147
00:18:50.955 --> 00:18:54.620
- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.

148
00:18:54.750 --> 00:18:56.161
Excellent choice.

149
00:18:56.961 --> 00:19:00.544
- I'll go!
- Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

150
00:19:00.673 --> 00:19:03.294
No! Not Vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

151
00:19:03.426 --> 00:19:06.510
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

152
00:19:14.186 --> 00:19:17.187
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

153
00:19:18.566 --> 00:19:22.610
And according to the bones.
that leader is...

154
00:19:23.738 --> 00:19:25.564
you. Burglekutt!

155
00:19:27.450 --> 00:19:29.241
Vohnkar!

156
00:19:30.328 --> 00:19:34.372
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

157
00:19:35.124 --> 00:19:39.750
When I held up my fingers.
what was your first impulse?

158
00:19:39.879 --> 00:19:42.915
- Well. it was stupid.
- Just tell me.

159
00:19:43.841 --> 00:19:46.414
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha!

160
00:19:46.552 --> 00:19:50.135
That was the correct answer.
You lack faith in yourself.

161
00:19:50.264 --> 00:19:53.051
More than anyone in the village...

162
00:19:53.184 --> 00:19:55.757
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

163
00:19:55.895 --> 00:20:00.604
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

164
00:20:02.401 --> 00:20:04.773
These will protect you.

165
00:20:04.904 --> 00:20:07.655
- Acorns?
- They're magic!

166
00:20:07.782 --> 00:20:11.649
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

167
00:20:14.830 --> 00:20:18.034
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

168
00:20:31.013 --> 00:20:32.721
Are you scared. Dada?

169
00:20:34.266 --> 00:20:35.429
No.

170
00:20:35.559 --> 00:20:37.599
Even with fairies in the woods...

171
00:20:37.728 --> 00:20:39.685
that'll put you to sleep
for a hundred years?

172
00:20:41.315 --> 00:20:43.853
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

173
00:20:43.984 --> 00:20:46.855
- Dragons?
- Trolls?

174
00:20:46.987 --> 00:20:50.356
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

175
00:20:50.533 --> 00:20:54.067
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

176
00:20:54.203 --> 00:20:56.659
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

177
00:20:56.789 --> 00:20:58.995
Me too. Me too. Dada.

178
00:21:00.584 --> 00:21:02.910
What a lucky father I am.

179
00:21:03.045 --> 00:21:05.797
I wish I could take
you bobbins with me.

180
00:21:09.009 --> 00:21:11.132
Goodbye. Dada.

181
00:21:13.764 --> 00:21:15.887
Go play! Go on.

182
00:21:21.397 --> 00:21:24.267
We've never been apart.

183
00:21:27.111 --> 00:21:29.353
I miss you already.

184
00:21:30.281 --> 00:21:32.108
Don't worry. Kiaya.

185
00:21:32.241 --> 00:21:36.108
I'll be fine. and I'll be back
before you know it.

186
00:21:38.497 --> 00:21:41.167
Well. remember to keep her warm.

187
00:21:43.252 --> 00:21:45.873
And here.

188
00:21:48.132 --> 00:21:50.884
This will bring you luck.

189
00:22:04.815 --> 00:22:07.306
Good brave people!

190
00:22:08.277 --> 00:22:10.946
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

191
00:22:11.071 --> 00:22:13.693
Give the baby
to the first Daikini you see...

192
00:22:13.824 --> 00:22:15.947
then hurry home.

193
00:22:19.330 --> 00:22:22.864
<i>Tuatha lawkathok tuatha!</i>

194
00:22:23.751 --> 00:22:26.456
Go in the direction
the bird is flying!

195
00:22:31.175 --> 00:22:33.333
It's going back to the village!

196
00:22:35.012 --> 00:22:37.218
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

197
00:22:37.348 --> 00:22:39.387
Move out!

198
00:23:03.541 --> 00:23:06.411
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

199
00:23:07.086 --> 00:23:09.292
We have to stop.

200
00:23:09.421 --> 00:23:11.046
Stop? Why?

201
00:23:11.173 --> 00:23:13.498
The baby's sick.

202
00:23:18.180 --> 00:23:20.718
She's not sick!
Let me see.

203
00:23:24.728 --> 00:23:26.768
Take her! Take her!

204
00:23:28.107 --> 00:23:31.108
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

205
00:23:34.488 --> 00:23:36.113
Clean me up.

206
00:23:39.410 --> 00:23:42.031
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

207
00:23:42.162 --> 00:23:45.662
- Sorsha. you're useless!
- I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

208
00:23:45.791 --> 00:23:48.282
I'll find where she hid the baby.

209
00:23:50.296 --> 00:23:52.502
Ah. General Kael. at last.

210
00:23:53.507 --> 00:23:57.291
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

211
00:23:57.428 --> 00:24:01.046
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

212
00:24:01.181 --> 00:24:06.602
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

213
00:24:06.729 --> 00:24:08.602
that continues somehow
to elude her.

214
00:24:10.649 --> 00:24:13.734
The baby of the prophecy?
The one that would destroy you?

215
00:24:13.861 --> 00:24:16.067
I need that baby alive.

216
00:24:16.196 --> 00:24:18.569
I must perform
the ritual that will exile...

217
00:24:18.699 --> 00:24:22.032
the child's spirit into oblivion.

218
00:24:22.161 --> 00:24:24.830
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

219
00:24:24.955 --> 00:24:26.912
You'll do as I say. child.

220
00:24:33.464 --> 00:24:35.587
I read the signs.

221
00:24:35.716 --> 00:24:38.836
One day. I fear.
your daughter will betray you.

222
00:24:38.969 --> 00:24:43.097
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

223
00:24:59.323 --> 00:25:01.150
Move!

224
00:25:01.909 --> 00:25:04.910
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

225
00:25:07.748 --> 00:25:09.372
Come on!

226
00:25:21.053 --> 00:25:22.927
The Nelwyns have got the baby.

227
00:25:23.055 --> 00:25:25.724
We've searched the village. but a group
of them are on the road somewhere.

228
00:25:25.849 --> 00:25:28.850
They couldn't have gone far!

229
00:25:28.977 --> 00:25:31.136
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

230
00:25:39.363 --> 00:25:41.521
Come.
We'll keep to the woods.

231
00:26:21.071 --> 00:26:22.565
That's it!

232
00:26:22.698 --> 00:26:24.737
It's the crossroads!

233
00:26:42.176 --> 00:26:45.461
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

234
00:26:51.477 --> 00:26:53.635
What was that?

235
00:26:54.772 --> 00:26:56.479
Get the spears!

236
00:27:15.083 --> 00:27:18.832
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

237
00:27:18.962 --> 00:27:21.334
Do you understand?

238
00:27:21.465 --> 00:27:23.292
Water.

239
00:27:25.969 --> 00:27:27.380
Hurry up!

240
00:27:31.517 --> 00:27:34.352
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks!

241
00:27:35.771 --> 00:27:37.894
It's a Daikini. We're in luck.

242
00:27:39.024 --> 00:27:42.060
- We can't give her to him!
- Somebody put him there for a reason.

243
00:27:42.194 --> 00:27:46.441
Ufgood. we've got to get rid of her.
Those soldiers are after us.

244
00:27:47.241 --> 00:27:49.992
He's looking right at us.

245
00:27:53.956 --> 00:27:55.948
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

246
00:27:56.708 --> 00:27:58.867
I'm somebody.

247
00:27:59.670 --> 00:28:02.706
Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby.

248
00:28:05.217 --> 00:28:07.506
I trust him completely.

249
00:28:07.636 --> 00:28:11.384
- But he tried to strangle me!
- I want to go home.

250
00:28:11.515 --> 00:28:15.098
No. Burglekutt!
We should wait!

251
00:28:15.227 --> 00:28:17.184
Are you challenging my authority?

252
00:28:17.312 --> 00:28:20.598
As far as this baby
is concerned. yes.

253
00:28:20.732 --> 00:28:23.733
Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.

254
00:28:25.028 --> 00:28:28.896
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

255
00:28:30.158 --> 00:28:32.946
That's a bad idea. Very bad.
Dangerous out there.

256
00:28:33.078 --> 00:28:37.076
- Get the gear. men.
- Vohnkar...

257
00:28:37.207 --> 00:28:42.332
- It's not his decision!
- Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

258
00:28:42.462 --> 00:28:46.246
- Don't let him talk to you that way.
- Listen here. runt.

259
00:28:46.383 --> 00:28:50.132
While you're wasting your time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.

260
00:28:50.262 --> 00:28:52.089
Think about it!

261
00:28:52.222 --> 00:28:56.350
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna...
- You're gonna what?

262
00:29:01.773 --> 00:29:04.609
Someday. Burglekutt.
Someday.

263
00:29:04.735 --> 00:29:06.644
Vohnkar. let's go!

264
00:29:10.198 --> 00:29:13.116
Meegosh. are you coming?

265
00:29:15.412 --> 00:29:17.037
I'm staying.

266
00:29:17.164 --> 00:29:18.955
Come on. men.

267
00:29:19.082 --> 00:29:23.210
Burglekutt. let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

268
00:29:24.046 --> 00:29:26.085
Just let me out of here.
Please!

269
00:29:26.214 --> 00:29:29.500
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear
just for a minute.

270
00:29:29.635 --> 00:29:31.841
Well. at least get me some water!

271
00:29:31.970 --> 00:29:34.888
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two!

272
00:29:39.394 --> 00:29:41.720
What'll we do now. Willow?

273
00:29:41.855 --> 00:29:44.428
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

274
00:29:44.566 --> 00:29:49.311
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry. peck.

275
00:29:49.446 --> 00:29:53.147
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

276
00:29:54.076 --> 00:29:56.911
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

277
00:29:58.455 --> 00:30:01.160
I'll throw it at you
and turn you to stone.

278
00:30:03.043 --> 00:30:04.917
I'm really scared.

279
00:30:05.087 --> 00:30:07.542
No. don't! Don't!

280
00:30:07.673 --> 00:30:10.757
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

281
00:30:11.635 --> 00:30:13.509
I wouldn't want to waste it!

282
00:30:15.555 --> 00:30:19.470
Peck. peck. peck. peck!

283
00:30:48.922 --> 00:30:50.915
What was that?

284
00:30:54.428 --> 00:30:56.883
Mornin'. boys.

285
00:30:58.181 --> 00:31:01.266
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

286
00:31:02.394 --> 00:31:05.679
I don't think
I introduced myself yesterday.

287
00:31:05.814 --> 00:31:09.230
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh...

288
00:31:09.359 --> 00:31:11.399
No. Meegosh.

289
00:31:11.528 --> 00:31:13.817
Don't go near him.
He's dangerous.

290
00:31:13.947 --> 00:31:15.774
I am not.

291
00:31:16.908 --> 00:31:18.984
Good.

292
00:31:22.789 --> 00:31:24.996
Stop! Wait!

293
00:31:35.844 --> 00:31:38.513
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

294
00:31:40.140 --> 00:31:42.133
I suppose you're a warrior.

295
00:31:42.267 --> 00:31:44.723
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

296
00:31:47.731 --> 00:31:51.349
Say. could I have
some of that water?

297
00:32:01.203 --> 00:32:03.491
I don't know why I try.

298
00:32:11.254 --> 00:32:13.959
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares?

299
00:32:14.090 --> 00:32:15.964
- Here.
- Thanks. friend.

300
00:32:17.761 --> 00:32:19.635
What's that?

301
00:32:19.763 --> 00:32:22.468
I'd say
two or three hundred horses...

302
00:32:22.599 --> 00:32:26.513
five or six wagons.
and about a thousand fools.

303
00:32:30.649 --> 00:32:33.021
- Thank you.
- Come on. Meegosh.

304
00:32:38.824 --> 00:32:41.112
It's gonna be all right.
little bobbin.

305
00:32:49.125 --> 00:32:50.952
Everything's gonna be all right.

306
00:32:54.381 --> 00:32:57.335
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

307
00:33:00.428 --> 00:33:02.504
Pardon me.

308
00:33:09.604 --> 00:33:11.312
Excuse me. sir.

309
00:33:12.524 --> 00:33:14.766
We found one of your babies
in our village.

310
00:33:14.901 --> 00:33:17.736
Will you please take care of her?

311
00:33:18.822 --> 00:33:22.155
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

312
00:33:23.368 --> 00:33:25.824
They thought you were
a woman. Airk.

313
00:33:26.955 --> 00:33:29.280
Well...

314
00:33:29.416 --> 00:33:31.907
Madmartigan!
What did you do this time?

315
00:33:32.043 --> 00:33:33.953
Nothing you wouldn't have done
in my place.

316
00:33:34.087 --> 00:33:36.578
I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

317
00:33:36.715 --> 00:33:39.881
At least I'm not herding sheep.
What are you doing this far north?

318
00:33:40.010 --> 00:33:42.927
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

319
00:33:43.054 --> 00:33:44.679
The castle?

320
00:33:44.806 --> 00:33:46.799
Bavmorda's troops are crushing
everything in sight.

321
00:33:46.933 --> 00:33:48.807
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

322
00:33:48.935 --> 00:33:51.094
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

323
00:33:51.229 --> 00:33:55.606
Madmartigan.
I still serve Galladoorn.

324
00:33:55.734 --> 00:33:57.643
You serve no one.

325
00:33:57.777 --> 00:33:59.984
Remember?

326
00:34:00.113 --> 00:34:02.153
Sit in your coffin and rot.

327
00:34:03.408 --> 00:34:06.409
Wait. Airk. You need me!

328
00:34:06.536 --> 00:34:08.908
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

329
00:34:09.039 --> 00:34:11.612
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...

330
00:34:11.750 --> 00:34:13.789
and stick it on a pig pole!

331
00:34:33.396 --> 00:34:35.934
I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

332
00:34:40.445 --> 00:34:42.485
We're running out of food.

333
00:34:45.325 --> 00:34:47.531
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

334
00:34:47.661 --> 00:34:50.496
You know why?
Nobody cares.

335
00:34:53.541 --> 00:34:55.581
Except me.

336
00:34:56.753 --> 00:35:01.296
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

337
00:35:01.424 --> 00:35:05.339
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

338
00:35:05.470 --> 00:35:08.388
I believe he would. Willow.

339
00:35:08.515 --> 00:35:11.006
He doesn't know anything
about babies.

340
00:35:12.018 --> 00:35:16.312
Right. but I know
a lot of women who do.

341
00:35:17.232 --> 00:35:19.308
If I had somebody in my life...

342
00:35:20.276 --> 00:35:22.981
a little daughter. perhaps...

343
00:35:23.113 --> 00:35:26.279
I might have a reason
to go on living.

344
00:35:29.619 --> 00:35:32.739
You can't leave me
in here to die.

345
00:35:32.872 --> 00:35:35.494
Not when all I want to do
is protect her.

346
00:35:48.888 --> 00:35:52.720
I feel better!

347
00:35:52.851 --> 00:35:56.516
- You've done the right thing!
- Okay. All right.

348
00:35:56.646 --> 00:35:58.555
You gotta promise to feed her.

349
00:35:58.690 --> 00:36:01.062
Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

350
00:36:01.192 --> 00:36:04.359
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

351
00:36:14.748 --> 00:36:16.574
She likes me.

352
00:36:18.710 --> 00:36:21.035
Here are her changing rags.

353
00:36:21.171 --> 00:36:23.294
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

354
00:36:23.465 --> 00:36:27.593
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

355
00:36:30.555 --> 00:36:32.927
You worry too much. peck.

356
00:36:33.058 --> 00:36:36.177
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

357
00:36:37.562 --> 00:36:40.480
Now listen. boys... Willow.

358
00:36:40.607 --> 00:36:42.765
You've done the right thing.

359
00:36:42.901 --> 00:36:46.151
Now I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

360
00:36:52.327 --> 00:36:54.652
Goodbye. little one.

361
00:37:05.840 --> 00:37:07.880
Please take good care of her.

362
00:37:10.261 --> 00:37:12.550
I give you my word of honour!

363
00:37:19.896 --> 00:37:23.182
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

364
00:37:23.316 --> 00:37:25.772
If we hurry. we could be home
by tomorrow morning.

365
00:37:25.902 --> 00:37:28.571
We'll be heroes.

366
00:37:28.696 --> 00:37:31.069
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

367
00:37:31.199 --> 00:37:33.405
"Look. there's Willow and Meegosh.

368
00:37:33.535 --> 00:37:35.741
The heroes have come home."

369
00:37:35.870 --> 00:37:38.871
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

370
00:37:38.998 --> 00:37:41.287
Yeah. medals!

371
00:37:49.008 --> 00:37:51.416
Did we do the right thing?

372
00:37:51.553 --> 00:37:54.388
Absolutely.
There's nothing to worry about.

373
00:38:02.814 --> 00:38:07.974
I stole the baby! I stole the baby!

374
00:38:10.530 --> 00:38:13.863
That's my baby!
Stop! Wait! Come back!

375
00:38:13.992 --> 00:38:17.028
Left. you stupid bird. Left!

376
00:38:23.710 --> 00:38:25.998
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

377
00:38:27.088 --> 00:38:30.255
Come on. Meegosh!

378
00:38:36.431 --> 00:38:38.470
We'll outrun 'em!

379
00:38:43.229 --> 00:38:45.269
Hey. ugly. wake up!

380
00:38:52.947 --> 00:38:55.106
Stand your ground.
These are our prisoners.

381
00:38:55.241 --> 00:38:57.993
Meegosh. where's the baby?

382
00:38:58.119 --> 00:39:01.286
<i>- Bring the Nelwyns to me.
- All right. you heard her!</i>

383
00:39:01.414 --> 00:39:05.115
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

384
00:39:05.251 --> 00:39:07.576
You are mine to toy with.

385
00:39:08.671 --> 00:39:11.162
Forward!

386
00:39:12.258 --> 00:39:14.167
Get the rope.

387
00:39:16.721 --> 00:39:21.466
Where did you get that baby?

388
00:39:21.601 --> 00:39:25.100
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

389
00:39:27.690 --> 00:39:32.317
<i>Franjean. release the Nelwyns.
and stop pestering them.</i>

390
00:39:49.212 --> 00:39:51.251
<i>Welcome to my kingdom.</i>

391
00:39:59.222 --> 00:40:03.683
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

392
00:40:04.477 --> 00:40:07.015
Elora Danan told me.

393
00:40:07.146 --> 00:40:10.313
Elora?
Elora. Willow is here.

394
00:40:14.112 --> 00:40:18.738
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

395
00:40:18.866 --> 00:40:23.279
My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.

396
00:40:25.123 --> 00:40:29.167
Elora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

397
00:40:29.294 --> 00:40:30.752
Me?

398
00:40:30.878 --> 00:40:34.294
Yes. She likes you.

399
00:40:35.466 --> 00:40:40.378
And Elora Danan knows
you have the courage to help us.

400
00:40:40.513 --> 00:40:44.048
Take my wand
to the sorceress Fin Raziel.

401
00:40:44.183 --> 00:40:48.395
She will guide you and Elora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen...

402
00:40:48.521 --> 00:40:51.557
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

403
00:40:51.691 --> 00:40:55.356
You need a warrior
for a job like this. I'm a nobody.

404
00:40:55.486 --> 00:40:58.820
Elora. you don't want me.

405
00:40:58.948 --> 00:41:02.566
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

406
00:41:06.873 --> 00:41:08.912
Hello?

407
00:41:15.590 --> 00:41:18.923
Elora Danan must survive!

408
00:41:19.052 --> 00:41:21.091
She must fulfil her destiny...

409
00:41:21.220 --> 00:41:23.890
and bring about the downfall
of Queen Bavmorda...

410
00:41:24.015 --> 00:41:26.767
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

411
00:41:26.893 --> 00:41:31.222
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...

412
00:41:31.356 --> 00:41:35.484
of your village.
your children... everyone.

413
00:41:40.573 --> 00:41:44.024
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

414
00:41:45.411 --> 00:41:47.902
The choice is yours.

415
00:42:12.522 --> 00:42:15.772
Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.

416
00:42:16.692 --> 00:42:19.729
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

417
00:42:23.741 --> 00:42:25.781
Listen. Meegosh.

418
00:42:25.910 --> 00:42:29.361
Tell Kiaya I love her
and I think of her every day.

419
00:42:31.958 --> 00:42:34.745
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

420
00:42:34.877 --> 00:42:37.451
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

421
00:42:38.840 --> 00:42:40.464
I hope so.

422
00:42:41.968 --> 00:42:44.044
Listen. be careful.

423
00:42:51.018 --> 00:42:54.601
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

424
00:42:54.730 --> 00:42:56.557
I am the leader!

425
00:42:56.691 --> 00:42:59.312
- How long will it take to find Raziel?
- Not long.

426
00:42:59.444 --> 00:43:02.777
She's been exiled to an island
just over those hills.

427
00:43:02.905 --> 00:43:05.776
- She's what?
- Exiled.

428
00:43:05.908 --> 00:43:08.993
By the evil Queen Bavmorda.

429
00:43:10.079 --> 00:43:12.653
Rool. you fool. He does not need
to know everything!

430
00:43:12.790 --> 00:43:15.328
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

431
00:43:15.460 --> 00:43:18.710
You mentioned the island.
you mentioned the queen.

432
00:43:19.088 --> 00:43:20.417
So?

433
00:43:20.548 --> 00:43:23.300
What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?

434
00:43:23.426 --> 00:43:25.999
Don't play with that wand.

435
00:43:26.137 --> 00:43:28.628
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

436
00:43:28.764 --> 00:43:34.007
Only a great sorcerer can use it.
not a stupid peck like you.

437
00:43:34.145 --> 00:43:37.229
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

438
00:43:37.356 --> 00:43:39.598
- All right. then this way.
- Nope.

439
00:43:39.734 --> 00:43:42.225
- This way.
- This way?

440
00:43:42.361 --> 00:43:46.027
- That's what I said.
- This way.

441
00:43:46.157 --> 00:43:48.066
Are you sure you know
where you're going?

442
00:43:48.201 --> 00:43:52.329
Of course. With us as your guides.
no harm will befall you.

443
00:44:09.138 --> 00:44:11.131
We are not going in there!

444
00:44:11.265 --> 00:44:14.183
But Elora needs fresh milk.
and we're drenched.

445
00:44:14.310 --> 00:44:17.596
You are not in command
here. shorty. I am!

446
00:44:17.730 --> 00:44:19.770
You hear me?

447
00:44:59.105 --> 00:45:01.477
Excuse me? Excuse me.

448
00:45:01.607 --> 00:45:04.525
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

449
00:45:04.652 --> 00:45:06.443
Get out of here. peck!

450
00:45:06.571 --> 00:45:09.358
Get outta here or we'll cook ya!

451
00:45:23.879 --> 00:45:26.168
Look at her!

452
00:45:26.299 --> 00:45:28.505
I could use a love potion on her!

453
00:45:28.634 --> 00:45:32.418
Franjean! Give me
that dust of broken heart.

454
00:45:32.555 --> 00:45:34.215
Come on! Give it to me!

455
00:45:34.348 --> 00:45:37.634
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

456
00:45:41.772 --> 00:45:43.848
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

457
00:45:50.865 --> 00:45:55.574
Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

458
00:45:59.248 --> 00:46:01.620
You are so beautiful!

459
00:46:03.210 --> 00:46:05.701
Your eyes!
Your whiskers!

460
00:46:05.838 --> 00:46:10.251
- I have to kiss you!
- Rool! That dust of broken heart!

461
00:46:25.191 --> 00:46:27.018
Beer!

462
00:46:30.488 --> 00:46:32.527
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

463
00:46:37.161 --> 00:46:41.075
Hurry! Hurry!
My husband's coming!

464
00:46:41.207 --> 00:46:43.199
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

465
00:46:43.334 --> 00:46:45.907
- How do I look?
- Not you!

466
00:46:47.171 --> 00:46:49.045
Where the hell did you come from?

467
00:46:49.173 --> 00:46:51.379
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

468
00:46:51.509 --> 00:46:53.003
Don't I know you?

469
00:46:53.135 --> 00:46:56.754
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.
while you were taking a pee-pee!

470
00:46:56.889 --> 00:46:59.925
- Cover your face!
- You are crawling with Brownies.

471
00:47:00.226 --> 00:47:02.764
I hate Brownies!

472
00:47:04.563 --> 00:47:06.805
- Where is he?
- Hello. dear.

473
00:47:06.941 --> 00:47:09.266
There's nobody here
but me and. uh. my...

474
00:47:09.402 --> 00:47:11.727
- I'll kill him!
- My cousin. Hilda.

475
00:47:11.862 --> 00:47:14.069
Hilda?

476
00:47:14.198 --> 00:47:16.903
Hilda. this is my husband. Llug.

477
00:47:17.034 --> 00:47:19.110
Big husband.
How do you do?

478
00:47:23.582 --> 00:47:27.746
- Come on. girly. Don't be shy.
- Give her back!

479
00:47:28.504 --> 00:47:30.829
- Pecks make such terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

480
00:47:30.965 --> 00:47:33.004
They get too excited.

481
00:47:33.926 --> 00:47:36.499
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

482
00:47:40.266 --> 00:47:42.139
Stop. please.

483
00:47:43.477 --> 00:47:46.431
Come on.
Fight like a man!

484
00:47:46.564 --> 00:47:48.391
Want to breed?

485
00:47:48.524 --> 00:47:51.478
Tempting. but no.

486
00:47:54.864 --> 00:47:57.437
- Thank you. Time to leave.
- Bye. Hilda!

487
00:47:57.575 --> 00:47:59.651
Take them out!

488
00:48:00.828 --> 00:48:04.244
Come along! Move along!

489
00:48:04.373 --> 00:48:07.042
Gather up all these babies.

490
00:48:07.168 --> 00:48:09.409
That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

491
00:48:13.174 --> 00:48:15.250
That's not the one.

492
00:48:19.013 --> 00:48:21.718
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

493
00:48:21.849 --> 00:48:24.387
- Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

494
00:48:24.518 --> 00:48:26.060
No! Don't let her!

495
00:48:27.730 --> 00:48:30.517
I gave you an order. woman!

496
00:48:41.702 --> 00:48:43.362
You're beautiful!

497
00:48:43.496 --> 00:48:46.781
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

498
00:48:49.794 --> 00:48:52.830
You're no woman!

499
00:48:52.963 --> 00:48:54.790
- Not a woman?
- Gentlemen...

500
00:48:54.924 --> 00:48:56.715
Not a woman?

501
00:48:56.842 --> 00:48:58.502
Meet Llug.

502
00:49:00.930 --> 00:49:02.922
- After them!
- Out of the way!

503
00:49:09.271 --> 00:49:10.434
To the horses!

504
00:49:23.035 --> 00:49:26.867
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

505
00:49:30.417 --> 00:49:32.825
He's not a woman!

506
00:49:39.426 --> 00:49:42.795
Madmartigan. stop!

507
00:50:01.824 --> 00:50:04.279
Madmartigan. I'm warning you...

508
00:50:07.621 --> 00:50:09.993
Prepare to die!

509
00:50:33.439 --> 00:50:35.727
Madmartigan! Stop!

510
00:50:51.790 --> 00:50:54.910
No more beer.

511
00:51:05.846 --> 00:51:07.839
Franjean. help me!

512
00:51:12.519 --> 00:51:15.390
- Rool! Rool!
- Help!

513
00:51:19.026 --> 00:51:22.477
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

514
00:51:27.910 --> 00:51:30.116
- Come on.
- Pull me in.

515
00:52:07.282 --> 00:52:10.782
Rool. this isn't funny!
Help me cut the rope!

516
00:52:48.282 --> 00:52:50.820
Willow. stay down!

517
00:52:54.580 --> 00:52:56.572
Whoa!

518
00:52:59.043 --> 00:53:00.869
Have you gone crazy?

519
00:53:01.003 --> 00:53:03.079
You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

520
00:53:03.213 --> 00:53:05.586
We're getting off!

521
00:53:39.249 --> 00:53:41.823
Now we stop. peck.

522
00:53:43.003 --> 00:53:45.459
Stupid Daikini!

523
00:53:45.589 --> 00:53:48.258
Ask him to stop the wagon.

524
00:53:48.383 --> 00:53:52.512
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

525
00:53:54.306 --> 00:53:56.512
I just saved that infant's life!

526
00:54:00.479 --> 00:54:02.353
Gather your wits. Come on.

527
00:54:02.481 --> 00:54:05.435
- Don't worry about me. I'm fine!
- Come on!

528
00:54:07.444 --> 00:54:08.689
Get down!

529
00:54:08.821 --> 00:54:11.146
Where am I?

530
00:54:13.117 --> 00:54:15.156
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

531
00:54:32.928 --> 00:54:35.763
You better clear out. Willow.
before those troops come back.

532
00:54:35.889 --> 00:54:39.305
- My head!
- We don't need him. Elora.

533
00:54:47.734 --> 00:54:49.774
Madmartigan. wait!

534
00:54:49.903 --> 00:54:53.189
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

535
00:54:53.323 --> 00:54:55.233
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

536
00:54:55.367 --> 00:54:58.534
My help?
What do you need my help for?

537
00:54:58.662 --> 00:55:00.738
You're a sorcerer!

538
00:55:00.873 --> 00:55:04.076
You're a great warrior
and a swordsman.

539
00:55:04.209 --> 00:55:07.044
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

540
00:55:08.213 --> 00:55:11.380
Are you trying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

541
00:55:15.971 --> 00:55:18.544
Hurry! Big dogs!

542
00:55:18.682 --> 00:55:22.846
Look. I'm sorry I got angry.

543
00:55:22.978 --> 00:55:24.887
We wouldn't have escaped
without you.

544
00:55:39.119 --> 00:55:41.906
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

545
00:55:43.457 --> 00:55:47.040
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

546
00:55:49.087 --> 00:55:51.543
That way.

547
00:55:51.673 --> 00:55:54.923
You are drunk. and when
you are drunk. you forget that...

548
00:55:55.052 --> 00:55:56.925
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

549
00:55:57.054 --> 00:55:59.212
Fine.
Then which way do we go?

550
00:56:00.557 --> 00:56:02.882
That way!

551
00:56:04.394 --> 00:56:08.890
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

552
00:56:09.024 --> 00:56:11.941
All right. all right.
You can follow me as far as the lake.

553
00:56:12.069 --> 00:56:14.192
But that's it!

554
00:56:14.321 --> 00:56:18.021
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

555
00:56:18.200 --> 00:56:19.528
Good.

556
00:56:19.660 --> 00:56:23.278
Mumbo. Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go get me some eggs or something.

557
00:56:23.413 --> 00:56:25.987
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

558
00:56:32.756 --> 00:56:36.291
Kael. have you found the child?

559
00:56:37.511 --> 00:56:40.180
The search goes on. my queen.

560
00:56:40.305 --> 00:56:42.298
Why. with my powers...

561
00:56:42.432 --> 00:56:45.599
with the strength
of my great army...

562
00:56:45.727 --> 00:56:49.061
can you not find
one little child?

563
00:56:49.189 --> 00:56:51.478
We look even now.
It won't be long.

564
00:56:51.608 --> 00:56:54.942
Find the child.
Find the child!

565
00:56:55.070 --> 00:56:57.608
Time is running out.

566
00:57:05.455 --> 00:57:07.946
- Good night.
- She is kinda cute.

567
00:57:09.710 --> 00:57:11.418
When she's quiet.

568
00:57:12.879 --> 00:57:14.753
She's really a princess.

569
00:57:14.881 --> 00:57:18.665
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

570
00:57:18.802 --> 00:57:20.842
And I'm the king of Kashmir.

571
00:57:21.805 --> 00:57:24.094
Go to sleep. Willow.

572
00:57:24.850 --> 00:57:27.305
Good night. Madmartigan.

573
00:57:27.436 --> 00:57:30.353
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

574
00:57:31.148 --> 00:57:33.140
Rats!

575
00:57:33.900 --> 00:57:38.693
Rool. you and
that stupid rat dream!

576
00:57:47.581 --> 00:57:50.286
<i>Tuatha...</i>

577
00:57:50.417 --> 00:57:52.493
<i>lawkathok...</i>

578
00:57:52.627 --> 00:57:54.501
<i>tuatha!</i>

579
00:58:03.805 --> 00:58:06.759
- There you are.
- Madmartigan!

580
00:58:08.226 --> 00:58:10.184
'Night. Willow.

581
00:58:22.366 --> 00:58:24.275
This way! This way!

582
00:58:36.171 --> 00:58:38.045
What are you doing?

583
00:58:38.173 --> 00:58:40.498
I found some black root.
She loves it!

584
00:58:40.634 --> 00:58:43.504
Black root?
I am the father of two children...

585
00:58:43.637 --> 00:58:45.546
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

586
00:58:45.680 --> 00:58:48.847
My mother raised us
on black root.

587
00:58:48.975 --> 00:58:51.466
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

588
00:58:51.603 --> 00:58:54.272
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

589
00:58:54.398 --> 00:58:57.268
She's Elora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

590
00:58:57.401 --> 00:58:59.689
And the last thing she's gonna want
is a hairy chest!

591
00:59:04.241 --> 00:59:07.692
Did you see what he did?
He stole our black root.

592
00:59:07.828 --> 00:59:09.867
I'll get some more.
Don't worry about it.

593
00:59:14.126 --> 00:59:16.367
There it is! The island!

594
00:59:20.132 --> 00:59:22.967
We made it.

595
00:59:23.093 --> 00:59:26.129
We have led you to the island
of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

596
00:59:26.263 --> 00:59:29.299
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat.

597
00:59:48.618 --> 00:59:53.079
- Well. looks like I got you here.
- You? What did you do?

598
00:59:53.206 --> 00:59:56.160
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs!

599
00:59:56.293 --> 00:59:59.662
- I found a boat. We're all set.
- Good.

600
00:59:59.796 --> 01:00:02.204
Take these two lizards out
and drown them.

601
01:00:02.340 --> 01:00:05.626
Lizards?
Who are you calling lizards?

602
01:00:07.762 --> 01:00:10.432
Your mother was a lizard!

603
01:00:13.435 --> 01:00:15.890
Goodbye. Sticks.

604
01:00:18.648 --> 01:00:21.483
If you really are a princess...

605
01:00:21.610 --> 01:00:23.649
take care of him.

606
01:00:31.578 --> 01:00:34.151
- Madmartigan!
- What?

607
01:00:35.165 --> 01:00:36.992
Thanks.

608
01:00:48.303 --> 01:00:51.589
- Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turn around!

609
01:00:54.226 --> 01:00:56.598
It's all right. Elora.

610
01:00:56.728 --> 01:00:59.682
Go to sleep.
Nobody'll find you here.

611
01:00:59.814 --> 01:01:02.352
I'll be back with Fin Raziel
very soon.

612
01:01:02.484 --> 01:01:05.734
We will guard her
with our meagre lives.

613
01:01:34.140 --> 01:01:35.967
Raziel!

614
01:01:37.018 --> 01:01:40.802
Fin Raziel!
I have to talk to you. please!

615
01:01:52.617 --> 01:01:54.740
She's not here.

616
01:02:00.834 --> 01:02:04.369
Get back! Who are you?

617
01:02:05.505 --> 01:02:08.340
Who are you?

618
01:02:10.844 --> 01:02:13.845
- I'm Willow Ufgood.
- What are you doing here?

619
01:02:13.972 --> 01:02:17.590
I've come to find
the great sorceress Fin Raziel.

620
01:02:17.726 --> 01:02:20.264
That's me! I'm Raziel!

621
01:02:22.314 --> 01:02:24.223
This can't be right!

622
01:02:24.357 --> 01:02:27.809
One of Bavmorda's spells
transformed me.

623
01:02:30.155 --> 01:02:32.693
Believe me.
it could have been worse!

624
01:02:34.284 --> 01:02:38.578
Well. this wand is for you.
It's from Cherlindrea.

625
01:02:38.705 --> 01:02:40.863
Then the prophecy is true.

626
01:02:40.999 --> 01:02:44.498
The princess has been born.
Take me to her.

627
01:02:48.506 --> 01:02:51.756
It is Elora Danan.
Isn't she beautiful?

628
01:02:53.636 --> 01:02:56.554
Isn't she beautiful?

629
01:02:56.681 --> 01:02:59.386
- That's Raziel?
- I don't know.

630
01:02:59.517 --> 01:03:02.388
I expected something
more grand. Less...

631
01:03:02.520 --> 01:03:04.478
- Fuzzy.
- Fuzzy.

632
01:03:04.606 --> 01:03:08.354
You must use the wand.
Turn me back into my human form.

633
01:03:08.485 --> 01:03:11.770
- What do I do?
- You mean you're not a sorcerer?

634
01:03:13.114 --> 01:03:15.522
Yes. Sorta.

635
01:03:15.658 --> 01:03:16.987
I'm a farmer.

636
01:03:18.286 --> 01:03:20.955
- But I do know a few tricks.
- Tricks?

637
01:03:21.081 --> 01:03:25.493
<i>Cherlindrea sent you?
You must learn real magic.</i>

638
01:03:27.420 --> 01:03:29.709
- Horses!
- Horses!

639
01:03:29.839 --> 01:03:32.128
Quick! Take her! Hurry!

640
01:03:41.184 --> 01:03:44.101
I knew he was a traitor!

641
01:03:46.773 --> 01:03:49.311
- Sorry about this. peck.
- Keep your mouth shut.

642
01:03:50.610 --> 01:03:53.183
I told you we'd find them
without your help.

643
01:03:53.321 --> 01:03:55.278
- Give me that baby!
- No!

644
01:03:58.785 --> 01:04:02.699
- Give her back!
- Leave me alone! Don't touch me!

645
01:04:08.670 --> 01:04:10.497
This is the one
we're looking for.

646
01:04:10.630 --> 01:04:12.670
We must take it back
to Nockmaar.

647
01:04:16.803 --> 01:04:18.677
Lose your skirt?

648
01:04:26.855 --> 01:04:29.856
- I've still got what counts.
- Not for long.

649
01:04:36.531 --> 01:04:39.022
- Bring him.
- Over here!

650
01:04:57.802 --> 01:05:00.258
We'll never keep up
with those horses.

651
01:05:01.014 --> 01:05:04.050
- Then we will have to track them.
- That would take forever.

652
01:05:04.184 --> 01:05:06.757
Besides. even if we find them.
they'll catch us...

653
01:05:06.895 --> 01:05:10.061
stick us in cages. torture us
and finally devour us.

654
01:05:10.190 --> 01:05:12.063
Are you suggesting we go home?

655
01:05:12.192 --> 01:05:14.943
- Nah. This is more fun.
- All right.

656
01:05:15.069 --> 01:05:17.027
Fine. then.
Come on.

657
01:05:30.960 --> 01:05:34.329
I'm worried about Elora.
She doesn't sound good.

658
01:05:34.464 --> 01:05:37.169
Hurry! Practise
the chant I taught you!

659
01:05:38.301 --> 01:05:40.874
<i>Tanna looatha...</i>

660
01:05:41.012 --> 01:05:43.052
I can't remember
the middle part.

661
01:05:43.181 --> 01:05:45.138
<i>Locktwaar!</i>

662
01:05:45.266 --> 01:05:48.267
That's the word
that pleads for change.

663
01:05:48.394 --> 01:05:50.352
<i>Locktwaar.</i>

664
01:05:53.983 --> 01:05:57.068
Elora's cold and hungry.
She knows me.

665
01:05:57.195 --> 01:05:59.104
Please. let me take care of her.

666
01:05:59.239 --> 01:06:01.315
I don't need help from a peck.

667
01:06:05.912 --> 01:06:08.996
- What are you staring at?
- Your leg.

668
01:06:10.166 --> 01:06:12.159
I'd like to break it.

669
01:06:12.293 --> 01:06:14.250
You may find that difficult.
slave...

670
01:06:14.379 --> 01:06:16.502
while I'm up here
and you're down there.

671
01:06:19.634 --> 01:06:21.840
I hate that woman.

672
01:07:00.425 --> 01:07:02.464
I found it. Kael.

673
01:07:04.929 --> 01:07:07.337
That should make
my mother happy.

674
01:07:07.473 --> 01:07:09.431
What are they gonna do to her?

675
01:07:23.031 --> 01:07:25.652
<i>Hither walha...</i>

676
01:07:25.783 --> 01:07:29.235
<i>bairn deru bordak...</i>

677
01:07:29.370 --> 01:07:30.699
<i>bellanockt.</i>

678
01:07:32.248 --> 01:07:34.205
That's magic?
Smells terrible.

679
01:07:34.334 --> 01:07:37.500
- It's the life spark. It forms after...
- It stinks!

680
01:07:37.629 --> 01:07:40.748
- This whole thing stinks!
- Ignore him. Willow.

681
01:07:40.882 --> 01:07:43.883
- He's a fool!
- If only I had a sword!

682
01:07:45.053 --> 01:07:47.045
If only you'd quit
talking about it.

683
01:07:47.180 --> 01:07:50.465
Willow. you must transform me
to my human self.

684
01:07:50.600 --> 01:07:53.387
But. Raziel. I'm not ready yet.

685
01:07:53.519 --> 01:07:56.686
You'd better be.
Get me down.

686
01:08:00.360 --> 01:08:01.688
Ow!

687
01:08:05.365 --> 01:08:08.365
Why don't you help me get out of here
instead of chattering with that muskrat?

688
01:08:08.493 --> 01:08:09.655
Muskrat!

689
01:08:09.786 --> 01:08:14.412
When I change back to my former self.
I will crush this army...

690
01:08:14.540 --> 01:08:17.956
and take Elora Danan
to Tir Asleen...

691
01:08:18.086 --> 01:08:20.624
where she will be safe.

692
01:08:21.464 --> 01:08:25.047
Ow! What'd you bite me for?

693
01:08:25.176 --> 01:08:28.426
You need three drops of your blood
to put in the potion.

694
01:08:28.554 --> 01:08:30.262
You could've warned me.

695
01:08:31.933 --> 01:08:34.305
For beginners.
there's some pain...

696
01:08:34.435 --> 01:08:39.477
but don't let anything
break your concentration.

697
01:08:44.654 --> 01:08:47.489
<i>Hither greenan bairn
claideb lunanockt.</i>

698
01:08:47.615 --> 01:08:51.280
- Hello. everybody! We have arrived!
- You are saved.

699
01:08:52.328 --> 01:08:54.202
Don't interrupt.

700
01:08:55.707 --> 01:08:58.826
<i>Hither greenan bairn
claideb lunanockt.</i>

701
01:08:59.669 --> 01:09:01.745
What will you look like
if this works?

702
01:09:01.879 --> 01:09:04.335
- Don't interrupt.
- Sorry.

703
01:09:04.465 --> 01:09:06.339
<i>Hither greenan bairn
claideb lunanockt.</i>

704
01:09:06.467 --> 01:09:09.717
I am a young. beautiful woman.

705
01:09:09.846 --> 01:09:11.589
Concentrate. Willow.

706
01:09:11.723 --> 01:09:13.845
<i>Hither greenan bairn
claideb lunanockt.</i>

707
01:09:16.436 --> 01:09:18.512
You're losing me!

708
01:09:19.689 --> 01:09:22.014
<i>Hither greenan bairn
claideb lunanockt.</i>

709
01:09:27.655 --> 01:09:29.861
You all right?
Nice try. Willow.

710
01:09:38.124 --> 01:09:41.991
Farmers!
Cherlindrea sends me farmers!

711
01:09:43.171 --> 01:09:45.578
The Nelwyn
really butchered that one.

712
01:09:45.715 --> 01:09:47.542
I'm sorry. Raziel.

713
01:09:47.759 --> 01:09:49.217
You want out?

714
01:09:49.343 --> 01:09:51.917
Easy. We can pick a lock.
Come on.

715
01:09:52.054 --> 01:09:53.762
No. No. no.
Like this!

716
01:09:53.890 --> 01:09:55.929
I know what I'm doing.
It's my spear. Leave it alone.

717
01:09:56.058 --> 01:09:58.384
Let me do it.

718
01:09:58.519 --> 01:10:00.393
Out of the way. rodents.

719
01:10:01.689 --> 01:10:02.804
Take your hand off that.

720
01:10:02.940 --> 01:10:07.318
You leave that alone.
you stupid. fat Daikini!

721
01:10:10.031 --> 01:10:12.356
Dust of broken hearts.

722
01:10:23.711 --> 01:10:25.455
You are free!

723
01:10:25.588 --> 01:10:26.703
Come on. Madmartigan.

724
01:10:26.839 --> 01:10:29.128
Let's get Elora Danan
out of here.

725
01:10:29.258 --> 01:10:31.085
Yeah.

726
01:10:31.219 --> 01:10:33.342
- It'll be fun.
- Come on.

727
01:10:45.691 --> 01:10:47.649
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

728
01:10:49.195 --> 01:10:51.271
I feel good.

729
01:10:51.405 --> 01:10:53.398
The dust of broken hearts.

730
01:10:55.034 --> 01:10:56.445
Come on!

731
01:11:03.042 --> 01:11:06.078
<i>- Let me see!
- Let me see. You always see.</i>

732
01:11:06.212 --> 01:11:08.620
There's Elora. right there.
on those furs.

733
01:11:11.092 --> 01:11:14.591
Hey. wait! Leave this to us.
It's too dangerous for you.

734
01:11:14.720 --> 01:11:18.884
Only one of us should go in there.
I know what I'm doing.

735
01:11:49.881 --> 01:11:52.502
Wait. No. no!

736
01:12:03.686 --> 01:12:06.473
- I love you.
- Madmartigan!

737
01:12:06.606 --> 01:12:09.523
What are you doing?
Get the baby!

738
01:12:09.650 --> 01:12:10.979
Come on!

739
01:12:26.500 --> 01:12:28.540
Wake from this hateful sleep.

740
01:12:28.669 --> 01:12:30.995
It deprives me of your beauty.

741
01:12:32.423 --> 01:12:35.839
- The beauty of your eyes...
- One move. jackass...

742
01:12:35.968 --> 01:12:38.803
and you really will be a woman.

743
01:12:38.930 --> 01:12:44.683
You are my sun! My moon!
My starlit sky.

744
01:12:44.810 --> 01:12:48.476
Without you. I dwell in darkness.
I love you.

745
01:12:50.024 --> 01:12:51.518
What are you doing here?

746
01:12:51.651 --> 01:12:54.936
Your power has enchanted me.
I stand helpless against it.

747
01:12:55.071 --> 01:12:56.944
Come to me now.

748
01:12:57.073 --> 01:12:59.480
Tonight. let me worship you
in my arms.

749
01:12:59.617 --> 01:13:02.286
- Get away from me!
- I love you!

750
01:13:02.411 --> 01:13:04.819
Stop saying that!

751
01:13:04.956 --> 01:13:09.167
How can I stop the beating of my heart?
It pounds like never before.

752
01:13:09.293 --> 01:13:11.831
- Out of fear.
- Out of love!

753
01:13:11.963 --> 01:13:14.418
I can stop it.
I'll kill you.

754
01:13:14.548 --> 01:13:16.588
Death. next to love.
is a trivial thing.

755
01:13:20.262 --> 01:13:22.718
Your touch is worth 100.000 deaths.

756
01:13:27.645 --> 01:13:29.187
What goes on here?

757
01:13:34.318 --> 01:13:36.275
Deceiver!

758
01:13:37.905 --> 01:13:39.696
Stop him!

759
01:13:48.708 --> 01:13:51.281
Get me out!

760
01:14:01.762 --> 01:14:03.802
<i>You are great!</i>

761
01:14:06.934 --> 01:14:08.594
Get on that shield!

762
01:14:25.953 --> 01:14:27.910
After them!

763
01:14:41.343 --> 01:14:42.719
They're getting away!

764
01:14:52.021 --> 01:14:54.179
- Follow me. Rool.
- Where are you?

765
01:14:54.315 --> 01:14:56.023
I don't know.

766
01:14:57.151 --> 01:14:59.108
Oh. no!
Where did everybody go?

767
01:14:59.236 --> 01:15:01.194
Maybe it was something we said.

768
01:16:40.963 --> 01:16:42.920
What the hell happened up there?

769
01:16:43.048 --> 01:16:45.088
You started spouting poetry.

770
01:16:45.217 --> 01:16:47.755
- Poetry?
- Yeah.

771
01:16:47.887 --> 01:16:50.971
"I love you. Sorsha.
I worship you. Sorsha."

772
01:16:51.098 --> 01:16:53.091
You almost got us killed!

773
01:16:53.225 --> 01:16:55.052
"I love you. Sorsha"?

774
01:16:55.186 --> 01:16:57.558
I don't love her.
She kicked me in the face.

775
01:16:57.688 --> 01:17:00.226
I hate her! Don't I?

776
01:17:03.319 --> 01:17:05.691
Kael! Kael!

777
01:17:05.821 --> 01:17:07.446
Nockmaar soldiers!

778
01:17:10.492 --> 01:17:12.615
Hide! Get the children!
Come on!

779
01:17:15.664 --> 01:17:17.990
- Hide! Get the children!
- They're after us!

780
01:17:18.125 --> 01:17:21.743
- We need a place to hide.
- Come on. Follow me. Quick!

781
01:17:38.312 --> 01:17:41.064
I knew you'd get out
of that rattrap.

782
01:17:43.567 --> 01:17:45.524
You left me to die. Airk.

783
01:17:45.653 --> 01:17:48.856
I probably saved your life.
We were slaughtered. and I lost a lot...

784
01:17:48.989 --> 01:17:49.903
Quiet!

785
01:17:52.493 --> 01:17:54.367
Tear this village apart!

786
01:17:55.120 --> 01:17:57.493
Look everywhere!

787
01:17:57.623 --> 01:17:58.821
Find the child!

788
01:18:34.702 --> 01:18:37.656
Tell Sorsha
I search the north bank!

789
01:18:37.788 --> 01:18:38.986
Yes. General.

790
01:18:52.845 --> 01:18:54.837
Quiet!

791
01:19:14.283 --> 01:19:17.237
- Sorsha!
- Back.

792
01:19:17.870 --> 01:19:18.984
Back!

793
01:19:25.753 --> 01:19:27.033
Back.

794
01:19:28.839 --> 01:19:31.840
- Keep the baby quiet.
- She needs to be changed.

795
01:19:32.676 --> 01:19:34.503
- Nockmaar scum!
- You'll never defeat us.

796
01:19:34.636 --> 01:19:36.296
- Give up the baby!
- Shut up!

797
01:19:38.390 --> 01:19:41.842
- Why does Bavmorda want this baby?
- She's a princess.

798
01:19:41.977 --> 01:19:44.646
- We're taking her to Tir Asleen.
- Tir Asleen?

799
01:19:44.772 --> 01:19:46.729
Even if you could find it. peck...

800
01:19:46.857 --> 01:19:49.182
she's right... you'd never
get past the Nockmaar army.

801
01:19:49.318 --> 01:19:53.150
There's an even bigger army
at Tir Asleen. if we can get there.

802
01:19:57.785 --> 01:20:00.489
I've lost more than half my men
fighting Bavmorda.

803
01:20:00.621 --> 01:20:02.578
Now you and this peck
are gonna take her on?

804
01:20:03.749 --> 01:20:06.454
You always told me you served
no one. Madmartigan.

805
01:20:06.585 --> 01:20:08.542
Since when are you a crusader?

806
01:20:10.839 --> 01:20:12.879
He's not gonna help you. peck.

807
01:20:14.176 --> 01:20:16.418
He's a worthless thief.

808
01:20:17.554 --> 01:20:19.962
I'm not a thief. Airk.

809
01:20:20.099 --> 01:20:21.676
He's not a thief.

810
01:20:24.269 --> 01:20:25.301
Are you?

811
01:20:39.910 --> 01:20:42.282
I serve the Nelwyn. Airk.

812
01:20:48.419 --> 01:20:50.992
- Want to come with us?
- You'll never make it.

813
01:20:53.006 --> 01:20:55.332
Then once again
we say goodbye.

814
01:21:08.730 --> 01:21:12.099
- Over here!
- Sorsha!

815
01:21:12.234 --> 01:21:14.476
Weapons down or she's dead!

816
01:21:29.084 --> 01:21:31.041
Get to your horses!
After them!

817
01:22:17.257 --> 01:22:19.713
This way!
This way!

818
01:22:19.843 --> 01:22:22.513
As the crow flies. you fools!

819
01:22:29.436 --> 01:22:32.223
- You're holding me too tight!
- I don't want you to get away.

820
01:22:32.356 --> 01:22:36.400
Why? Because I'm your sun.
your moon. your starlit sky?

821
01:22:38.779 --> 01:22:40.818
Get your hair out of my face
or I'll chop it off.

822
01:22:44.868 --> 01:22:46.576
Did I really...

823
01:22:46.703 --> 01:22:48.743
Did I really say
those things last night?

824
01:22:48.872 --> 01:22:51.957
- In your tent?
- You said you loved me.

825
01:22:52.084 --> 01:22:54.539
- I don't remember that.
- You lied to me!

826
01:22:54.670 --> 01:22:55.832
No. I...

827
01:22:57.130 --> 01:22:59.503
I just wasn't myself last night.

828
01:22:59.633 --> 01:23:03.251
I suppose my power enchanted you
and you were helpless against it.

829
01:23:04.596 --> 01:23:06.755
- Sort of.
- Then what?

830
01:23:07.933 --> 01:23:11.218
- It went away.
- Went away?

831
01:23:11.353 --> 01:23:14.270
"I dwell in darkness without you."
and it went away?

832
01:23:14.398 --> 01:23:16.106
Yeah.

833
01:23:37.713 --> 01:23:39.539
Hurry! Kael's coming!

834
01:23:44.136 --> 01:23:46.378
Madmartigan. come on! Now!

835
01:23:54.438 --> 01:23:56.229
Madmartigan. come on!

836
01:23:58.108 --> 01:24:00.860
They're coming! Away!

837
01:24:00.986 --> 01:24:02.149
Go on!

838
01:24:20.297 --> 01:24:21.839
Whoa! Whoa!

839
01:24:23.467 --> 01:24:24.961
This way!

840
01:24:31.141 --> 01:24:34.925
Tir Asleen!
At last. Tir Asleen!

841
01:24:45.864 --> 01:24:47.192
Hello?

842
01:24:49.159 --> 01:24:50.701
Hello?

843
01:24:54.873 --> 01:24:56.248
Hello?

844
01:24:58.168 --> 01:25:00.789
Why did I listen to you. peck?

845
01:25:00.921 --> 01:25:04.372
"Everything will be all right
once we get to Tir Asleen."

846
01:25:05.300 --> 01:25:08.135
The only army around is the one that's
about to ride across this valley...

847
01:25:08.261 --> 01:25:10.088
and wipe us out!

848
01:25:10.222 --> 01:25:13.223
But Cherlindrea said
we'd be safe here.

849
01:25:14.017 --> 01:25:17.054
Safe? Look at these people.

850
01:25:17.187 --> 01:25:21.054
This place is cursed. peck.
It's falling apart. Open your eyes!

851
01:25:21.191 --> 01:25:22.519
And it...

852
01:25:24.903 --> 01:25:26.896
Trolls.

853
01:25:29.950 --> 01:25:31.989
I hate trolls.

854
01:25:32.786 --> 01:25:35.158
This is the work of Bavmorda.

855
01:25:44.381 --> 01:25:46.919
Willow? The wand.

856
01:25:47.050 --> 01:25:50.384
- Turn me back into my human form.
- Are you sure?

857
01:26:08.655 --> 01:26:09.770
Good.

858
01:26:17.372 --> 01:26:19.412
Hurry. Willow.
Transform me.

859
01:26:19.541 --> 01:26:22.458
I can't do it.
I'm just not a sorcerer.

860
01:26:22.586 --> 01:26:28.422
But you can be.
Speak and be one with the words.

861
01:26:28.550 --> 01:26:31.670
<i>Avalorium greenan...</i>

862
01:26:32.220 --> 01:26:35.091
<i>luatha tye...</i>

863
01:26:35.223 --> 01:26:37.928
Oh. Willow. you're losing me.

864
01:26:42.230 --> 01:26:44.472
Madmartigan. Kael's coming!

865
01:26:44.608 --> 01:26:48.902
- Willow. you idiot.
- Raziel?

866
01:26:49.863 --> 01:26:52.354
Arm that catapult up there.

867
01:27:14.012 --> 01:27:17.713
Good work. Madmartigan.

868
01:27:17.849 --> 01:27:19.509
What happened to you?

869
01:27:19.643 --> 01:27:22.216
Assault!
Sorsha. battering ram!

870
01:27:27.442 --> 01:27:28.901
Cut it down!

871
01:27:40.956 --> 01:27:41.951
Faster!

872
01:27:57.514 --> 01:27:59.803
Forward! Break it down!

873
01:28:20.412 --> 01:28:22.903
Again! Again!

874
01:28:27.586 --> 01:28:29.993
Willow. use the wand
on that troll.

875
01:28:32.299 --> 01:28:33.674
<i>Bellalockt!</i>

876
01:28:56.865 --> 01:29:00.316
Break it down! Forward!

877
01:29:47.540 --> 01:29:49.913
Get him!

878
01:30:11.773 --> 01:30:13.397
The other side!

879
01:30:28.081 --> 01:30:30.323
Destroy the beast!
Find the baby!

880
01:30:31.418 --> 01:30:33.078
Take that!

881
01:32:09.265 --> 01:32:11.970
Madmartigan. help!

882
01:32:23.321 --> 01:32:25.064
Get him. Madmartigan!

883
01:32:35.375 --> 01:32:36.869
Here.

884
01:32:53.434 --> 01:32:54.715
The baby!

885
01:33:56.623 --> 01:33:59.742
Airk's army. Get Kael!

886
01:33:59.876 --> 01:34:02.201
Airk's army!

887
01:34:04.714 --> 01:34:06.837
- We are here!
- You are rescued!

888
01:34:06.966 --> 01:34:09.884
- Charge!
- Charge!

889
01:34:26.861 --> 01:34:29.186
No mercy!

890
01:34:42.669 --> 01:34:44.495
Elora!

891
01:34:45.797 --> 01:34:46.959
Willow!

892
01:34:53.429 --> 01:34:55.386
- Elora's gone.
- Willow.

893
01:34:56.557 --> 01:34:59.558
They've taken her.
There were too many of them.

894
01:35:04.899 --> 01:35:06.856
Can you ride?

895
01:35:10.113 --> 01:35:11.571
Let's ride.

896
01:35:24.043 --> 01:35:26.368
I have the child!

897
01:35:50.862 --> 01:35:52.938
We need towers
and a battering ram!

898
01:35:53.072 --> 01:35:56.157
Break out the tents!
Make camp!

899
01:35:56.284 --> 01:35:58.323
Make camp!

900
01:35:58.453 --> 01:36:00.244
We'll assault at first light.

901
01:36:14.093 --> 01:36:16.086
Where's Sorsha?

902
01:36:17.263 --> 01:36:20.050
She has turned against us.
Your Highness.

903
01:36:24.187 --> 01:36:26.594
Turned against me?

904
01:36:30.234 --> 01:36:32.310
Prepare for the ritual!

905
01:36:55.927 --> 01:36:58.215
This is not an army.

906
01:37:01.474 --> 01:37:04.095
Quick. Hide.

907
01:37:08.940 --> 01:37:11.976
Use the shelter chant.
Protect yourself.

908
01:37:12.110 --> 01:37:14.067
- Why?
- Just do it.

909
01:37:19.700 --> 01:37:24.161
- We've come for Elora Danan.
- You dare to challenge me?

910
01:37:24.288 --> 01:37:26.530
You're not warriors.

911
01:37:28.209 --> 01:37:29.537
You're pigs!

912
01:37:45.434 --> 01:37:47.226
You're all pigs!

913
01:37:49.230 --> 01:37:50.428
Pigs!

914
01:37:56.946 --> 01:37:59.863
<i>Avaggdu luatha bairn
off haefermore.</i>

915
01:38:08.708 --> 01:38:10.866
Sorsha!

916
01:38:12.003 --> 01:38:13.413
Mother. no!

917
01:38:16.591 --> 01:38:17.836
<i>Kothon!</i>

918
01:38:39.405 --> 01:38:42.940
<i>Avaggdu luatha bairn
off haefermore.</i>

919
01:38:57.632 --> 01:38:59.292
Begin the ritual.

920
01:38:59.425 --> 01:39:02.212
This baby will not destroy me.

921
01:39:06.807 --> 01:39:08.432
Come. thunder!

922
01:39:10.603 --> 01:39:12.477
Come. lightning!

923
01:39:13.314 --> 01:39:16.979
Touch this altar
with your powers.

924
01:39:40.341 --> 01:39:43.508
We've come all this way
and now Elora Danan's gonna die!

925
01:39:43.636 --> 01:39:46.506
No. we can still defeat Bavmorda.

926
01:39:46.639 --> 01:39:48.715
She's too powerful. Raziel.

927
01:39:48.849 --> 01:39:51.969
Transform me.
and I will destroy her.

928
01:39:57.358 --> 01:40:01.190
Elements of eternity.
above and below.

929
01:40:02.196 --> 01:40:05.980
Balance of essence.
fire beget snow.

930
01:40:07.535 --> 01:40:10.655
<i>- Locktwarr danalora luatha danu...
- Willow...</i>

931
01:40:10.788 --> 01:40:12.781
<i>- believe in the words.
- tuatha. tuatha...</i>

932
01:40:12.915 --> 01:40:15.074
<i>- Concentrate.
- chnox danu.</i>

933
01:40:15.209 --> 01:40:16.834
<i>Locktwarr danalora...</i>

934
01:40:16.961 --> 01:40:20.828
<i>- luatha danu tuatha. tuatha.
- Oh. no!</i>

935
01:40:28.097 --> 01:40:33.257
Don't give up. Willow!

936
01:41:14.435 --> 01:41:18.349
- Has it been so long?
- I'm sorry.

937
01:41:20.733 --> 01:41:24.184
Willow. we have work to do.

938
01:41:25.488 --> 01:41:27.231
Give me the wand.

939
01:41:27.990 --> 01:41:31.489
We must undo Bavmorda's sorcery.

940
01:41:34.372 --> 01:41:36.411
Let them in now.

941
01:41:41.170 --> 01:41:44.539
<i>Tuatha grin chnox
y foel famau.</i>

942
01:41:58.687 --> 01:42:01.807
Black fires
forever kindled within...

943
01:42:01.941 --> 01:42:04.183
let the second rite begin.

944
01:42:22.002 --> 01:42:23.034
Quick. inside.

945
01:42:24.046 --> 01:42:26.502
That won't breach the wall.
We can't get inside.

946
01:42:26.632 --> 01:42:29.550
- Elora Danan will die...
- Unless we save her.

947
01:42:29.677 --> 01:42:32.049
- Bavmorda's too powerful.
- No!

948
01:42:32.930 --> 01:42:37.509
She cannot transform you again.
My spell is protecting this camp.

949
01:42:37.643 --> 01:42:39.683
But can your magic
get us inside the fortress?

950
01:42:41.939 --> 01:42:43.682
We can't do it.

951
01:42:43.816 --> 01:42:45.440
Wait!

952
01:42:45.568 --> 01:42:48.604
Back home in my village.
we have a lot of gophers.

953
01:42:48.737 --> 01:42:51.063
- Willow. this is war. not agriculture.
- I know.

954
01:42:51.198 --> 01:42:54.283
But I have an idea
how to get inside the castle.

955
01:42:58.956 --> 01:43:01.957
<i>Ocht veth bordak stira.</i>

956
01:43:02.084 --> 01:43:04.658
<i>Ocht veth bordak stira.</i>

957
01:43:13.053 --> 01:43:16.054
Madmartigan. you and I are soldiers.
The peck's plan will never work.

958
01:43:17.725 --> 01:43:20.891
If the baby dies.
all hope for the future is lost.

959
01:43:23.314 --> 01:43:25.141
I'm going to fight.

960
01:43:28.652 --> 01:43:30.479
Me too.

961
01:43:37.870 --> 01:43:40.787
All right. we've got to decide
who's gonna go and who's gonna stay.

962
01:44:30.881 --> 01:44:35.757
Willow. all these years
I have waited to face Bavmorda.

963
01:44:35.886 --> 01:44:38.377
It is you
that has made this possible.

964
01:44:39.765 --> 01:44:43.977
Whatever happens.
I shall always admire you.

965
01:44:54.697 --> 01:44:56.985
Your children...

966
01:44:57.116 --> 01:44:59.785
will come to remember this day.

967
01:45:10.337 --> 01:45:13.338
We call upon you to surrender!

968
01:45:15.509 --> 01:45:17.466
We are all-powerful sorcerers.

969
01:45:18.554 --> 01:45:22.053
Give us the baby.
or we'll destroy you!

970
01:45:28.314 --> 01:45:30.805
Kill them!

971
01:45:50.085 --> 01:45:51.710
Patience. Willow.

972
01:45:53.631 --> 01:45:55.291
Courage. Willow.

973
01:46:11.398 --> 01:46:13.438
Back to the castle!

974
01:46:39.051 --> 01:46:42.301
<i>Ocht veth nockthirth bordak!</i>

975
01:46:42.429 --> 01:46:46.261
Exile the child to the 13th night.

976
01:46:54.024 --> 01:46:55.435
This way!

977
01:47:34.857 --> 01:47:41.109
<i>Nockthirth
plankton firth foreth forewar.</i>

978
01:47:41.238 --> 01:47:43.480
<i>Ocht veth nock!</i>

979
01:47:43.615 --> 01:47:46.106
It's all right. Willow.

980
01:47:46.243 --> 01:47:48.117
You don't have to go.

981
01:47:48.245 --> 01:47:51.032
Light the 13th candle!

982
01:48:06.013 --> 01:48:07.756
Raziel.

983
01:48:07.890 --> 01:48:09.265
Mother!

984
01:48:13.395 --> 01:48:17.856
Traitor child.
I must despise you now.

985
01:48:48.305 --> 01:48:51.306
- I won't let you kill that child.
- Away!

986
01:48:51.433 --> 01:48:52.808
<i>Avaggdu...</i>

987
01:48:53.769 --> 01:48:56.342
<i>strokt!</i>

988
01:49:12.871 --> 01:49:16.323
Your powers have gained
in strength. Raziel.

989
01:49:16.458 --> 01:49:21.583
I have Cherlindrea's wand.
Bavmorda.

990
01:49:23.882 --> 01:49:27.880
Elora Danan will be queen.

991
01:49:40.899 --> 01:49:42.097
Now you die!

992
01:49:46.530 --> 01:49:49.531
<i>Furrochk flarem!</i>

993
01:50:19.605 --> 01:50:21.846
<i>Claideb cla...</i>

994
01:50:23.567 --> 01:50:27.018
<i>Clai main!
Lunano ockht!</i>

995
01:50:29.031 --> 01:50:31.866
<i>Bachktu inno!</i>

996
01:52:23.729 --> 01:52:24.808
Airk!

997
01:52:28.108 --> 01:52:30.017
